1) Clone the app:
git clone git://github.com/real-travel/hotel_api_example_ruby.git

2) Install libxml-ruby, and geo-kit ruby gems

3) Configure your local database:
 a) Rename the config/database.yml.example to config/database.yml
 b) Change the database configuration to suit your needs
 c) Create the databases: rake db:create
 d) Run migrations: rake db:migrate

4) Load example data:
  rake app:import_places

5) Setup API Settings
  a) Rename the config/hotel_api.yml.example to config/hotel_api.yml
  b) replace the "example_id" with the aid (affiliate_id) that was given to you by Real Travel
